 0151: 
 0152:     """    
 0153:     Tile coding for function approximation (Supervised Learning).  
 0154:     Fits by averaging and/or Stochastic Gradient Descent.
 0155:     Supports multi-core fit and predict. Options for uniform, random or 'optimal' displacement vectors.
 0156:     Provides option for linear spline extrapolation / filling (suitable for small data sets)
 0157:     Optimises over first dimension (by grid search) subject to supplied constraints.
 0158: 
 0159:     Parameters
 0160:     -----------
 0161:     
 0162:     D : integer
 0163:         Total number of dimensions (e.g., action + state dimensions)
 0164:     
 0165:     T : list of integers, length D
 0166:         Number of tiles per dimension 
 0167:     
 0168:     L : integer
 0169:         Number of tiling 'layers'
 0170: 
 0171:     mem_max : double, (default=1)
 0172:         Proportion of total tiles to store in memory: less than 1 means hashing is used.
 0173:     
 0174:     min_sample : integer, (default=50) 
 0175:         Minimum number of observations per tile
 0176: 
 0177:     offset : string, (default='uniform')
 0178:         Type of displacement vector one of 'uniform', 'random' or 'optimal'
 0179: 
 0180:     lin_spline : boolean, (default=False)
 0181:         Use sparse linear spline model to extrapolate / fill empty tiles
 0182: 
 0183:     linT : integer, (default=6)
 0184:         Number of linear spline knots per dimension
 0185:     
 0186:     Attributes
 0187:     -----------
 0188: 
 0189:     N : integer
 0190:         Number of samples
 0191: 
 0192:     X : array, shape=(N, D)
 0193:         Input data (unscaled) (e.g., state-action samples, with action as first dimension X[:,0])
 0194: 
 0195:     Y : array, shape=(N) 
 0196:         Output data (unscaled), (e.g., Q samples)
 0197: 
 0198:     a : array, shape=(D) 
 0199:         Minimum of tiling range in each dimension (observations outside of range are ignored)
 0200:     
 0201:     b : array, shape=(D) 
 0202:         Maximum of tiling range in each dimension (observations outside of range are ignored)
 0203:     
 0204:     R2 : array, shape=(D) 
 0205:         Score (r-squared)
 0206:     
 0207:     """
 0208:
